@startuml Storage Enforcement - B2C vs B2B Comparison
!theme default
title Storage Enforcement System - B2C Hard vs B2B Soft Enforcement Models

package "B2C Hard Enforcement" as B2C {
  component [Individual Users\nwith Subscription] as B2CUsers

  card "Configuration" as B2CConfig {
    **enforcement_type:** hard
    **warning_threshold:** 75%
    **critical_threshold:** 90%
    **hard_limit:** 100%
    **grace_period:** 7 days
    **warning_frequency:** daily
  }

  component [Enforcement Timeline] as B2CTimeline {
    rectangle "0-75%" {
      color: #90EE90
      [✅ Plenty of storage\nUpload: allowed\nNotifications: none]
    }
    rectangle "75-90%" {
      color: #FFD700
      [⚠️ Getting full\nUpload: allowed\nNotifications: daily]
    }
    rectangle "90-100%" {
      color: #FFA500
      [⚠️ Almost full\nUpload: allowed_with_warning\nNotifications: daily_critical]
    }
    rectangle "100%+" {
      color: #FF6B6B
      [🚫 BLOCKED\nUpload: blocked\nGrace Period: 7 days active]
    }
    rectangle "7 days expired" {
      color: #8B0000
      [🛑 READ-ONLY MODE\nUpload: blocked\nDownload: readonly only\nAction: contact support]
    }
  }

  note bottom of B2CTimeline
    **Characteristics:**
    ✓ **Strict:** Quota enforcement at 100%
    ✓ **Quick:** Only 7 days to clean up
    ✓ **Aggressive:** Daily warnings
    ✓ **No overflow:** Hard limit at 100%
    Use case: Individual subscription users
  end note
}

package "B2B Soft Enforcement" as B2B {
  component [Organisations\n(Schools, Companies)] as B2BOrgs

  card "Configuration" as B2BConfig {
    **enforcement_type:** soft
    **warning_threshold:** 85%
    **critical_threshold:** 95%
    **hard_limit:** 110%
    **grace_period:** 30 days
    **warning_frequency:** weekly
  }

  component [Enforcement Timeline] as B2BTimeline {
    rectangle "0-85%" {
      color: #90EE90
      [✅ Plenty of storage\nUpload: allowed\nNotifications: none]
    }
    rectangle "85-95%" {
      color: #FFD700
      [⚠️ Getting full\nUpload: allowed\nNotifications: weekly]
    }
    rectangle "95-110%" {
      color: #FFA500
      [⚠️ Above 100%\nUpload: allowed_with_warning\nNotifications: weekly\nSuggest: contact admin]
    }
    rectangle "110%+" {
      color: #FF6B6B
      [📢 Request quota increase\nUpload: blocked\nGrace Period: 30 days active\nAction: admin intervention]
    }
    rectangle "30 days expired" {
      color: #8B0000
      [🛑 READ-ONLY MODE\nUpload: blocked\nDownload: allowed\nAction: must contact support]
    }
  }

  note bottom of B2BTimeline
    **Characteristics:**
    ✓ **Lenient:** Allows up to 110% before blocking
    ✓ **Patient:** 30 days to resolve
    ✓ **Collaborative:** Suggests admin action
    ✓ **Flexible:** Can adjust quotas dynamically
    Use case: Organisations with IT support
  end note
}

note right
  **Key Differences:**

  | Aspect | B2C Hard | B2B Soft |
  |--------|----------|----------|
  | Warning Threshold | 75% | 85% |
  | Critical Threshold | 90% | 95% |
  | Hard Limit | 100% | 110% |
  | Grace Period | 7 days | 30 days |
  | Warning Frequency | daily | weekly |
  | First Upload Block | 100% | 110% |
  | Target Users | Individuals | Organisations |
  | Flexibility | Limited | High |

  **B2C Philosophy:**
  Strict enforcement for fairness
  across all individual users

  **B2B Philosophy:**
  Flexible enforcement with
  administrative controls
end note

@enduml
